@node WYLW "WhateverYouLike-Ware"

WhateverYouLike-Ware
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This program is WhateverYouLike-Ware. This is similar to Shareware,
Freeware, Charityware, Beerware, and the million other variants. PLEASE
distribute the program as widely as you can. PLEASE include this document
file with it. You don't need to include the dictionary files, since it has a
small one built in, but PLEASE include the Amos.library, 'cause it won't run
without it. PLEASE do NOT distribute a modified version of the program, and
PLEASE don't distribute any dictionary files with *nasty* words in them.
Thank you. Sorry about the capital letters.

If you like it, please send me WhateverYouLike. If you think it's worth it,
send me some money - Hey, I sure could use it! - If you really like it, you
could send me a new Amiga or a Lamboghini :-) But even if you don't think
it's worth it, I'd appreciate a letter, a postcard or an e-mail so I can see
what people think of it.

If you send me a blank disk and return postage, or enough money to cover
buying a disk and posting it, I'll send it back with any updates of this
program on it, plus a few other programs I've written. Alternatively,
you could e-mail me for an update, or just download it from my web site.

Updates to this program depend on it's getting a reasonable response.


** @{b}Added 12-Feb-98:@{ub} Since the first release of HAL9001, this program
has generated a bigger response than any of my other programs, even being
mentioned in one magazine, and included on the cover CD of another.
I'd like to thank everyone who sent me an email about this program. You
gave me loads of ideas for it, which I'm just begining to implement.
Keep the encouragement flowing...!  Thank you.

