@node Versions

Version Notes:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
(not all versions or changes may be listed... just the ones I remember to
 make a note of...)


1.0:
Sentence producer created using basic linking of Noun Verb Noun.
Version 1.0 not released.

1.1:
Added command set accessed by # or *
Added adjectives, adverbs & posessive pronouns.
Added ability to handle verbs in past and future tenses.
Bug fix: Crashed when verb zero (to be) entered by user as part of sentence.
Bug fix: Crashed when computer tried to use pronoun "it" in sentence.
Also several minor fixes and speed improvements.
Version 1.1 received a very limited release.

1.2:
Noun1 and noun2 now agree (ie singular or plural) when the verb is "To Be".
   (ie: you no longer get "I am many people." etc)
Added autosaving and #autosave command.
Added "Dictionary not saved..." when quitting, and #check command.
Added #print command.
Added #version command.
Added #cls command
Fixed a couple of minor bugs.
Partially disabled #correct command due to serious bugs.
Turned HAL9001.Doc into HAL9001.guide - looks really good!

1.21:
(First public release - homepage and Aminet)
Added #show command.
Fixed a couple of bugs.
Changed my address in docs.

1.23:  12-February-1998.
(homepage release only - no Aminet release)
Added #topic command
Fixed a few bugs
Started work to enable "question" sentences ("what.....?", etc)
Started work to enable "quantatives" (ie "a pair of...", etc)

1.30:  24-July-1998.
(released to some reg users)
Added ability to ask questions.  ("Is he going..?", "Did the dog..?", etc)
Added #question command to control them.
Fixed one or two bugs.

1.31:  28-July-1998.
(Aminet & registered users release)
Slight improvements to questions system. (It now asks "Why did they.." as
 well as simply "Did they...")

1.32:  08-August-1998.
(Aminet release)
Bug fix: 1.31 didn't work. Oops. Thanks to everyone who reported the problem.

1.33:  08-August-1998. (busy day!)
(Registered users release)
Added #log command, and log file generation. You can now keep a record of
 your conversations with HAL, without having to print them.  ;-)

1.34:  29-September-1998.
(released only on my web site)
A few smallish bug-fixes.
Started prototyping a new 'save preferences' feature.

1.40:  11-October-1998.
(not released)
Added ability for prefs to be stored in tooltypes. Now you don't have to
 re-set all your settings every time. And it's easy to use, too.  ;-)
 That's a big enough change for me to bump the version up to 1.40.  :-)
Added chapter in this document for the prefs.

1.41:  18-October-1998.
(not released)
More work to the prefs.

1.42:  20-October-1998.
(released everywhere)
Added a new command #PALETTE & the coresponding tooltype, after many hints
 from a certain registered user who didn't like the colour-scheme <grin>.
 See the appropriate parts of this guide for more info.

No more changes. 20-October-1998.

