@endnode

@node Future

Plans for the future
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
This program is very much an experiment. I am enjoying the challenge of
writing it, and I have some quite ambitious plans for versions to come.

For the next version (or the one after that...)
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Fix all the bugs (naturally <grin>).
   Fix #correct command. (or improve the auto-correction! <grin>)
   Add ability to recognise proper names, etc.
   Add an option to change the maximum dictionary size (from prefs/tooltype?)
   Add an optional third noun (and other words) to sentences for longer
       sentences. eg: "The man played the tape @{b}with his stereo@{ub}." etc...
                                               ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
                                                /
                                      This is the bit I'd have to add.

Put those together, and we could get some very, very long sentences!
Here's a possible example to whet your appetite...
  "Mr Fred Jones is going to wear his pair of shoes without a pair of socks."

.....

Ok, so it's a bit of a ridiculous sentence, but then what do you expect from
a computer??

For versions in the far distant future:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Anyone like to see voice recognition? Ha! Not for a while, I'm afraid!
   Add an ability to recognise facts, to deduce other facts from the facts
       input, and output the deductions.

Hmmmm...... Then again, maybe not...   ;-)

... Ok. Look, if you really want me to work on that sort of thing, you'd
better tell me!

If anyone else has anything they'd like to see that I haven't mentioned yet,
please feel free to drop me a line (see my @{"address" link Address}). Give me some really
good ideas - I might even mention you in the credits!
The same applies to bugs: You see 'em, please report them to me.
The same applies again if you have any ideas for any other programs you'd

Footnote: Just in case you thought you could get away without contacting me,
you should know that every update released so far has been a direct result
of someone (or several people) telling me what they think of it.
Knowing that there's an audience out there makes such a difference  :-)
Go on! How long does it take to knock up a quick email?


            @{"Version history " link Versions}

            @{"Back to begining" link Main}
@endnode
